-- Patriots' Running Back Faulk to Miss Season With Knee Injury, ESPN Reports
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2010-09-22T16:22:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/patriots-running-back-faulk-will-miss-season-with-knee-injury-espn-says.html
New England Patriots running back
Kevin Faulk will miss the remainder of the season after injuring
his right knee against the New York Jets on Sept. 19, ESPN
reported, citing an unidentified person in the National Football
League.  Faulk, 34, had run for 45 yards this year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  